---
// No props
---
<section class="bg-neutral px-5 sm:px-12 py-12 sm:py-16 border-t-2 border-primary border-b-2">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 md:gap-16 items-start">
    <!-- Left: copy -->
    <div>
      <p class="text-[0.625rem] text-primary font-bold tracking-[2px] uppercase mb-[0.875rem]">
        Built for Maine
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-[2rem] sm:text-[2.5rem] font-black text-white leading-[1.2] mb-5 text-balance">
        Your site should load even with two bars.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[0.8125rem] text-white/70 leading-[1.9] mb-6 text-pretty">
        You know how you pull up a local business on your phone and it just… sits there?
        That's not a you problem — it's how the site was built.<br /><br />
        Most sites around here are slow because they're built on old platforms packed
        with things nobody needs. I build differently — leaner, faster. The kind of site
        that loads before your visitor gives up.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap gap-2">
        {['Loads on weak cell signal', 'Photos load sharp, not slow', 'Works on any phone', 'Served from everywhere'].map(tag => (
          <span class="border border-primary/40 px-4 py-2 text-[0.6875rem] text-white/70">{tag}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- Right: speed bars -->
    <div>
      <p class="text-[0.625rem] text-white/55 mb-5 tracking-[1px] uppercase">
        Google speed score · Mobile
      </p>
      <!-- Typical site bar -->
      <div class="mb-[1.625rem]">
        <div class="flex justify-between mb-2">
          <span class="text-xs text-white/65">Typical local site</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-[#e05252]">~45 / 100</span>
        </div>
        <div
          role="progressbar"
          aria-valuenow="45"
          aria-valuemin="0"
          aria-valuemax="100"
          aria-label="Typical local site Google mobile speed score: 45 out of 100"
          class="bg-white/[0.08] h-[0.625rem]"
        >
          <div class="h-full w-[45%] bg-[#e05252]"></div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[0.625rem] text-white/55 mt-[0.3125rem]">Takes 7–8 seconds to show anything on mobile</p>
      </div>
      <!-- Wolff Digital bar -->
      <div class="mb-2">
        <div class="flex justify-between mb-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-white/80">Wolff Digital standard</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-primary">95+ / 100</span>
        </div>
        <div
          role="progressbar"
          aria-valuenow="96"
          aria-valuemin="0"
          aria-valuemax="100"
          aria-label="Wolff Digital standard Google mobile speed score: 95 or higher out of 100"
          class="bg-white/[0.08] h-[0.625rem]"
        >
          <div class="h-full" style="width:96%;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#ebbb40,rgb(0,245,184))"></div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[0.625rem] text-white/65 mt-[0.3125rem]">Under 1 second to start showing content</p>
      </div>
      <!-- Guarantee box -->
      <div class="mt-2 p-[1.125rem] border border-primary/40">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold text-primary mb-[0.3125rem]">Written into every contract.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-white/65 leading-[1.6]">
          If your site doesn't hit 95 or higher before launch, we don't launch.
          Not a target — a guarantee.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
